spans.text: Fortune gentle , at the hill's verge extreme , Arrayed in decent garb , but somewhat thin
no fairy lights , no quickening ray , Nor stir of pulse , nor objects
pagod in a nitch Obscure , or grandees with nod-watching eye
to bed Lethargic , which at intervals the sick Hears and forgets
why sweet slumbers wait The hard pallet ? not because from haunt remote Sequestered in a dingle's bushy lap : It's labour makes the peasant's savoury fare
fallacious she pretend From worldly bondage to set free , what gain Her votaries
we that man with vigorous power endowed , And room to stretch
up to the terms on which they hold Their vital lease
which they hold Their vital lease
such the tenure of our earthly state
The nimble runner courses Fortune down
of some Assiduous booby mounting over your head
that Time Has golden minutes , if discreetly seized
